\begin_inset Formula $\{x_{n}\}\subset<a,b>$
\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula $\lim_{k\rightarrow\infty}x_{n_{k}}=x_{0}\implies\lim_{k\rightarrow\infty}f(x_{n_{k}})=f(x_{0})\iff\forall_{\epsilon>0}\exists_{k_{0}\in\mathbb{N}}\forall_{k\ge k_{0}}|f(x_{n_{k}})-f(x_{0})|<\epsilon$
